Code examples for observer pattern in C++11 blog entry, 

http://juanchopanzacpp.wordpress.com/2013/02/24/simple-observer-pattern-implementation-c11/

Requirements: 

* a reasonably C++11 compliant compiler. Tested with g++ 4.7.2 and a 4.8 snapshot, on various linux distrobutions.
* gnu make (optional, for building)

Runnable examples are called exampleN.cpp, where N is positive integer. To build using make:

> make example<N>
